Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potato{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, sprinkle over half of the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1} and toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.
> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Fried Chicken ==

In the meantime, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @Panko Breadcrumbs{50%g} into another #bowl{}, mix with the remaining
@Thai Style Spice Mix{1}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Season the @British Chicken Thighs{3}, then dip into the egg and then the
breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of
the pan.
> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for about 2-3
> minutes before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the frying pan and fry until
golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray, then bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Sweet Chilli Slaw ==

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In a large bowl, mix together the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, sliced baby gem,
@mayonnaise{32%g} and half of your @sweet chilli sauce{64%g}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Set aside.

Wipe out the frying pan used for the chicken, then heat on medium-high heat with
a drizzle of @oil{}.

== Peanut Sauce ==

Once the pan is hot, add the @red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and fry until fragrant,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @peanut butter{30%g}, @water for the Sauce{75%ml} and the remaining sweet
chilli sauce. Whisk until smooth. Simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}. Set aside.

Meanwhile, if you have a #microwave{}, place the @bao buns{4}(2 per person) on
your now clean plate and microwave, 750W ~{1%minute} 30 secs, 900W ~{1%minute}.
If you don't, place the bao buns onto a baking tray. Bake the bao buns on the
middle shelf until warm and fluffy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven and cut each thigh into 2-3
pieces (depending on size).

When ready, transfer your bao buns to your #serving plates{} and fill with your
fried chicken pieces and a spoonful of slaw. Drizzle over your peanut sauce.

Serve your chips, remaining slaw and any remaining peanut sauce alongside.

Enjoy!